sentences:
Clarence Profit ( June 26 , 1912 – October 22 , 1944 ) was a jazz pianist and composer associated with swing .
He came from a musical family and began studying piano at the age of three and he led a ten - piece band in New York City in his teens .
A visit to his grandparents in Antigua resulted in his staying in the Caribbean for five years .
He also led a group in Bermuda .
He returned to the US and led a trio .
He co - composed " Lullaby In Rhythm " with Edgar Sampson .
He was respected in his era , but after his early death fell into obscurity .
He was born , and died , in New York City .
